[[File:Aleksandr Dulitšenko.JPG|thumb|Aleksandr Dulitšenko (2005)]] '''Aleksandr Dmitrievich Dulichenko''' (alternatively Alexander Duličenko; {{lang-ru|Александр Дмитриевич Дуличенко}}) (born 1941)<ref name="suspicious document" /> is a [[Russians in Estonia|Russian-Estonian]] [[Esperantist]], linguist, and an expert in [[Slavic microlanguages]] currently living in [[Estonia]].<ref name="suspicious document">[http://www.garshin.ru/linguistics/model/_doc/authors/dulichenko.doc Biography of Dulichenko] (in Russian).</ref> He is a professor at the [[University of Tartu]] in [[Tartu]], where he is the head of the department of Slavic studies.<ref>[http://www.ut.ee/FLVE/ Branch of Russian and Slavic Philology, Tartu University] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090328051057/http://www.ut.ee/FLVE/ |date=2009-03-28 }}. (In Russian.)</ref>
Dulichenko was born in [[Krasnodar]].<ref name="suspicious document" /> He is the editor of ''Interlinguistica Tartuensis'', a journal on [[interlinguistics]] published by the University of Tartu that published seven volumes from 1982 to 1990 recording the proceedings of colloquia at Tartu;<ref>{{citation|first=Detlev|last=Blanke|url=http://www.interlinguistik-gil.de/scholit.html|title=Interlinguistics and Esperanto studies: Paths to the scholarly literature|journal=Language Problems & Language Planning|volume=28|year=2003|issue=2|pages=155–192}}</ref> in 2006, an eighth volume was published.<ref>[http://www.esperantic.org/dosieroj/file/IpI56.pdf IpI 56 (1/2006)], {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718054352/http://www.esperantic.org/dosieroj/file/IpI56.pdf |date=2011-07-18 }} p. 12.</ref> A [[festschrift]] in Dulichenko's honor was organized in 2006;<ref>{{citation|first1=Ago|last1=Kunnap|first2=S. N.|last2=Kuznetsov|first3=Werner|last3=Lehfeldt |title=Mikroiazyki, Iazyki, Interiazyki : Sbornik V Chest Ordinarnogo Professora Aleksandra Dmitrievicha Dulichenko |publisher=[[Tartu Ulikool]], Slaavi Filoloogia Oppetool |location=[[Tartu]] |year=2006|isbn=9949-11-444-6}}.</ref> [[Humphrey Tonkin]] calls this volume a "particularly important addition to the literature" of interlingual and [[esperantology|Esperanto studies]].<ref>{{citation | title=Recent Studies in Esperanto and Interlinguistics: 2006| first=Humphrey |last =Tonkin | authorlink =Humphrey Tonkin | journal =[[Language Problems and Language Planning]] | volume =31| year =2007 |issue =2 |pages=169–195|url =http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/jbp/lplp/2007/00000031/00000002/art00004 }}.</ref>
